news.title: Nashik civic body chief seeks large residential project data
news.para: Jadhav gave the instructions following allegations by some parties that some plots meant for houses for economically weaker sections (EWS) were used for residential projects with commercial purposes.

news.title: Google to open new office in Pune later in 2022
news.para: "Recruiting starts now though alongside the organization’s rapidly growing teams in Gurgaon, Hyderabad and Bangalore," the Mountain View headquartered technology giant said in a statement.

news.title: Nitin Gadkari urges construction sector to substitute diesel with alternative fuels
news.para: ​Addressing an event organised by industry body CII, Gadkari said currently India is importing 85 per cent of its crude oil requirement, which amounts to Rs 8 lakh crore annually, which is a huge burden on the economy.

news.title: Pune civic body extends waiver plan for property tax defaulters
news.para: The Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) had introduced the amnesty scheme for property tax defaulters. 75% waiver on the penalty will be given to defaulters if they pay the levy under this initiative.

news.title: Maharashtra sets up committee to probe map forgery case
news.para: The panel will scrutinise over 800 maps for the Madh Island and Erangal village area that have allegedly been manipulated, and inquire whether constructions were built with or without BMC permission. In cases of violation, it will direct the BMC to take action.

news.title: IPO-bound OYO gets listing approval from BSE, NSE
news.para: OYO has filed preliminary documents for a Rs 8,430 crore initial public offering (IPO). The offering will consist of a fresh issue of shares of up to Rs 7,000 crore and an offer-for-sale of as much as Rs 1,430 crore.

news.title: Indiabulls Real Estate posts Rs 87 crore loss in Q3 Fy22
news.para: Total income fell to Rs 355.59 crore in the third quarter of this fiscal, from Rs 756.81 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Elan group buys 40-acre land from Indiabulls Real Estate for Rs 580 crore
news.para: In a regulatory filing, IBREL said the board has approved the divestment of 100 per cent stake in its four subsidiaries which own the land parcel at Sector 106, Gurugram.

news.title: Macrotech Developers' profit up 24% at Rs 286 crore in Q3 FY22
news.para: Total income increased to Rs 2,148.74 crore during the October-December quarter of this fiscal year as against Rs 1,599.77 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Chinese state-owned property firms step in to rescue cash-strapped builders
news.para: State-owned China Overseas Land & Investment (COLI) is buying stakes of Shimao Group and Agile Group in a joint venture project for a total of 3.7 billion yuan ($585 million).

news.title: Noida: D-day nearing, nervousness and relief at Supertech Emerald Court
news.para: On the Supertech Emerald Court compound is palpable relief about finally seeing towers that dwarfed the rest of the complex go.

news.title: Rental income of malls may fall 24% in Q4 to around Rs 300 crore due: ICRA
news.para: When contacted, ICRA Sector Head (Corporate Ratings) Anupama Reddy said the rental collection of these 23 malls could drop by 24 per cent from an estimated Rs 400 crore in the previous quarter.

news.title: Specialized safety audits for high-risk jobs may reduce accidents at construction sites
news.para: As per a study published in 2015 in the Scientific World Journal, the Indian construction labour force which is 7.5% of the total world labour force, contributes to 16.4% of fatal global occupational accidents.

news.title: 14 FIRs against touts, staff of Bangalore development body for fraud in online plot sale
news.para: Sources in the BDA said they had put up plots for auction at Arkavathi Layout, Anjanapura, Banashankari, JP Nagar, newly-formed Nadaprabhu Kempegowda Layout, Nagarabhavi, HBR Layout and Sir M Visvesvaraya Layout.

news.title: Portal to monitor dust pollution launched in Haryana
news.para: Created on the directions of the CAQM, the portal features a live dashboard to reflect ambient air quality status at specific construction sites once the registrations, mandatory for any site that’s more than 500 square metres in area, are complete.
